Verse 1:
Yo, let me tell you a tale 'bout the rap karma,
Where the truth cuts deep like a katana, (karma)
In this game, we rise or fall, no in-between,
What you sow, you reap; it's written in the scene. (karma)

[Powerpop Chorus]
See, the mic's like a mirror, reflecting your soul,
Spit lies on the track, and you'll lose all control, (karma)
You can front, you can fake, but it won’t last long,
'Cause karma's got a rhythm, and it’s stronger than your song. (karma)

[Bass Drop]
You diss on the real ones, claim you’re the king,
But the crown’s heavy, and it’s weighing down your bling, (karma)
Haters throwing shade, thinking they’re the best,
But the universe is watching, putting them to the test. (karma)

Chorus:
I am your karma, the echo in your verse, (karma)
The beat of your downfall, the blessing or the curse, (karma)
You can't outrun it, no matter where you go,
What you give to the world, it’ll come back in flow. (karma)

Verse 2:
Remember when you laughed, left me out in the cold,
Thought I’d never shine, thought I’d never be bold, (karma)
But I kept my grind tight, lyrics pure as gold,
Now the tables have turned, and the truth’s been told. (karma)

[Bass Drop]
See, I move with the grace of divine intervention,
Every word I drop, a holy redemption, (karma)
For every hater’s plot, for every fake smile,
Karma’s got a tally, and she’s been watching for a while. (karma)

[Powerpop Chorus]
You stole the style, tried to claim it as your own,
But authenticity’s a seed that must be sown, (karma)
Now your kingdom crumbles, built on lies and deceit,
Karma’s coming for you, and she’s got you on repeat. (karma)

Chorus:
I am your karma, the echo in your verse, (karma)
The beat of your downfall, the blessing or the curse, (karma)
You can't outrun it, no matter where you go,
What you give to the world, it’ll come back in flow. (karma)

Bridge:
You see, karma's not a thing you can buy or sell,
It’s the whispers of truth that your ego can't quell, (karma)
It’s the path that you chose when you stepped in the game,
It’s the fire that burns in the heart of your name. (karma)

You can stunt, you can shine, but if your spirit's hollow,
The shadow of your past will be the one you follow, (karma)
So be careful where you tread, in the booth or the street,
Karma’s in the cypher, and she’s moving to the beat. (karma)

[Melodic Bass]
Now I'm the voice you ignored, the talent you dissed,
But now I’m the storm that you can’t resist, (karma)
The truth in my flow, like a river, it rolls,
Washing away all the grime from your soul. (karma)

[Outro]
So to all the real ones, keep your game tight,
And to the snakes in the grass, stay out of sight, (karma)
Karma’s on the prowl, and she’s ready to strike,
In this world of rap, only the true ones take flight. (karma)
